[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment with caregiver setup, longitudinal-coordination-state initialization, cross-organizational data ingestion, seam-detection and protocol-driven trigger evaluation, channel entry, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-coordination-context loading, conversation handling with protocol-grounded responses, output safety screening, and care-team reporting with outcome correlation. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (cross-organizational data integration with provenance, longitudinal-coordination-state-as-system-of-record, referral-and-transition-of-care state machines, seam-detection rule engine with clinical-leadership ownership, and caregiver-as-first-class-participant identity model).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CAREGIVER SETUP ──────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via primary care home, payer,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-management program, or coordination service]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to coordination work     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with cross-organizational data integration scope     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      explicit                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver designation captured (zero or more         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      caregivers, each with proxy-access scope)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Known clinicians captured (each with organization,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      role, primary contact, EHR identifier where known)   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Known pharmacies captured                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Known payers captured                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Known ancillary services captured (home health,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      DME, infusion, dialysis, lab, imaging)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient and caregiver preferences captured           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (channels, quiet hours, language, preferred name,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      what to discuss with whom)                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - State-specific consent variations enforced for       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      sensitive record categories (mental health, HIV,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      substance use under 42 CFR Part 2, genetic test      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      results, adolescent confidentiality)                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed consent records; coordination           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    enrollment record; caregiver-access records]           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── LONGITUDINAL COORDINATION STATE INIT ──────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient-coordination longitudinal state]               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active conditions registry (synthesized across       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      sources)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active medication list (synthesized across           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pharmacies and clinicians)                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open-referrals registry with lifecycle state         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Upcoming-encounters list                             │
